1
00:04:11,066 --> 00:04:12,818
Hey, let's go to Grandma.

2
00:04:12,818 --> 00:04:13,944
Oh, there's Grandma.

3
00:04:16,901 --> 00:04:17,901
Blessie...

4
00:04:17,905 --> 00:04:19,489
- Grandma!
- Agatha...

5
00:04:22,742 --> 00:04:25,244
- Hey, look.
- Wow. Sis, it's so cute!

6
00:04:25,244 --> 00:04:27,288
Oh my God, a dollhouse.

7
00:04:27,288 --> 00:04:28,456
- It's pretty
- I want it.

8
00:04:28,456 --> 00:04:29,624
- What now?
- So cute!

9
00:04:29,624 --> 00:04:31,959
Let’s try again.
Okay, come on.

10
00:04:32,502 --> 00:04:33,544
Who will play?

11
00:04:33,544 --> 00:04:36,099
- Me! I'm the best player here.
- Geez!

12
00:04:36,106 --> 00:04:37,219
- I'll play, my dear.
- Let me.

13
00:04:37,227 --> 00:04:38,570
- I will play.
- Grandma, let me.

14
00:04:38,579 --> 00:04:39,579
Give me the balls.

15
00:04:39,604 --> 00:04:40,884
- Let Grandma do it.
- Let me. I'll play.

16
00:04:40,891 --> 00:04:42,500
No. I'll play.
[phone ringing]

17
00:04:42,525 --> 00:04:43,525
I already have it.

18
00:04:43,813 --> 00:04:46,036
Hi, baby. How are you guys doing?

19
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:47,687
Good morning, Mommy.

20
00:04:47,687 --> 00:04:49,439
Here's our target prize.

21
00:04:49,439 --> 00:04:51,024
Grandma's already playing.

22
00:04:52,607 --> 00:04:54,383
Hi, Blessie, my dear!

23
00:04:54,388 --> 00:04:56,397
Did you not go to work?

24
00:04:56,402 --> 00:04:58,979
Hmm. You're at the fair again.

25
00:04:59,003 --> 00:05:00,003
Mm-hmm.

26
00:05:00,017 --> 00:05:01,185
Okay, look.

27
00:05:01,185 --> 00:05:02,506
Watch and learn.

28
00:05:02,530 --> 00:05:03,530
Okay. Go, Grandma!

29
00:05:03,543 --> 00:05:04,543
Go, Grandma!

30
00:05:04,544 --> 00:05:06,004
[Blessie & Agatha] Woah!

31
00:05:06,748 --> 00:05:07,999
Wow!

32
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:11,270
Hey you guys, you're
tiring your grandma out.

33
00:05:11,651 --> 00:05:13,930
What do you think of me? Weak?
Here's another.

34
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:15,504
- One more, Grandma. One more.
- Go, Grandma!

35
00:05:16,202 --> 00:05:18,496
[Blessie & Agatha] Woah!

36
00:05:18,796 --> 00:05:20,502
Good job, Grandma.

37
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:23,405
Hey, love. Are you riding
the tube to work?

38
00:05:23,429 --> 00:05:24,699
- Yes.
- Coffee, love.

39
00:05:24,706 --> 00:05:27,119
- Go, Grandma!
- Good morning, Neville, my love.

40
00:05:28,104 --> 00:05:29,188
Let's go!

41
00:05:31,103 --> 00:05:32,999
- Oh.
- What a shame.

42
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,769
Don't worry.
We'll get it next time.

43
00:05:37,407 --> 00:05:38,992
You may get three.

44
00:05:39,197 --> 00:05:41,283
Hey, don’t be sad.

45
00:05:41,283 --> 00:05:43,744
First of all, your grandma
is already tired.

46
00:05:43,744 --> 00:05:45,454
Besides, me and your...

47
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:49,128
Uncle Neville will buy
the dollhouse for you.

48
00:05:49,737 --> 00:05:51,406
At least we got candies.

49
00:05:52,002 --> 00:05:53,002
My dear,

50
00:05:53,027 --> 00:05:55,213
why don't you introduce us to…

51
00:05:55,213 --> 00:05:56,465
your devil?

52
00:05:57,174 --> 00:05:58,303
Ma!

53
00:05:58,310 --> 00:05:59,937
It's Neville, not devil.

54
00:05:59,937 --> 00:06:01,564
He might hear you.

55
00:06:03,207 --> 00:06:05,418
Alright, Ma. I’ll go ahead.

56
00:06:05,442 --> 00:06:06,485
Okay, Mommy.

57
00:06:06,485 --> 00:06:07,993
Bye-bye. Love you!

58
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,661
I love you, my girls.

59
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:11,223
Take care, okay?

60
00:06:11,490 --> 00:06:13,200
I will. Ma...

61
00:06:13,492 --> 00:06:15,995
don’t be stubborn and take a rest.

62
00:06:17,212 --> 00:06:19,381
Sis, let's just go on rides.

63
00:06:19,656 --> 00:06:21,203
- Shall we? Let's go!
- Yeah.

64
00:06:21,210 --> 00:06:22,674
Grandma, wait a sec.
We’re just going for a ride.

65
00:06:22,676 --> 00:06:24,425
Come on, hurry, this way!
Where do you want?

66
00:06:24,436 --> 00:06:25,462
There!

67
00:06:25,467 --> 00:06:26,552
Alright. Here first!

68
00:06:32,228 --> 00:06:33,813
Grandma, let’s go!

69
00:06:34,380 --> 00:06:35,654
Grandma, come!

70
00:06:35,678 --> 00:06:37,563
Just give me a second.

71
00:06:37,572 --> 00:06:39,273
I’ll buy some pancit.

72
00:06:39,286 --> 00:06:40,475
- For long life.
- Ah, pancit.

73
00:06:40,719 --> 00:06:42,069
- Okay, sure!
- Will buy pancit?

74
00:06:42,073 --> 00:06:44,062
- Mm-hmm. Pancit for long life.
- Pancit…

75
00:06:47,508 --> 00:06:49,093
Grandma, are you okay?!

76
00:06:52,555 --> 00:06:53,555
Grandma?!

77
00:06:53,556 --> 00:06:54,556
Grandma. Agatha.

78
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:55,683
- Grandma!
- Sis!

79
00:06:55,683 --> 00:06:58,561
Grandma! Grandma!

80
00:06:58,561 --> 00:07:00,563
- Sis, I’ll call a tricycle.
- Call a tricycle.

81
00:07:00,563 --> 00:07:02,106
Tricycle! Help us!

82
00:07:02,106 --> 00:07:03,902
Grandma! Grandma,
don’t close your eyes!

83
00:07:03,909 --> 00:07:05,921
Grandma, can you hear me?

84
00:07:05,929 --> 00:07:07,177
I’m here, Grandma!

85
00:07:07,184 --> 00:07:08,720
Grandma!
We’re going to the hospital.

86
00:07:08,727 --> 00:07:10,114
- Let's go home.
- Help!

87
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,093
Tricycle. Help!
Please help us!

88
00:07:12,093 --> 00:07:13,791
Sir, please help us!

89
00:07:13,798 --> 00:07:15,602
Grandma!

90
00:07:15,606 --> 00:07:16,715
Grandma!
[indistinct chatters]

91
00:07:16,721 --> 00:07:19,015
Grandma! Grandma!
[indistinct chatters]

92
00:07:19,015 --> 00:07:20,606
Sir, please take it easy!

93
00:07:20,613 --> 00:07:21,685
Grandma!

94
00:07:22,060 --> 00:07:23,812
I’ll take care of the house.

95
00:07:23,812 --> 00:07:25,438
Bring grandma to the hospital.

96
00:07:25,981 --> 00:07:27,232
[Blessie & Agatha] Grandma!

97
00:07:27,232 --> 00:07:28,601
- We’re getting on.
- Please be careful!

98
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:29,651
Let’s get on.

99
00:07:29,651 --> 00:07:31,278
Watch her head! Steady.

100
00:07:32,779 --> 00:07:34,739
Grandma, please wake up.

101
00:07:34,739 --> 00:07:36,032
Don’t close your eyes.

102
00:07:36,032 --> 00:07:37,784
We’re almost there.

103
00:07:41,978 --> 00:07:43,394
Check the IV,

104
00:07:43,418 --> 00:07:45,048
oximeter,

105
00:07:45,072 --> 00:07:46,507
and blood pressure.

106
00:07:48,603 --> 00:07:51,063
Inform me immediately if there
are any changes in the

107
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,806
[phone ringing]
- vital signs.

108
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:54,602
Call the ICU as well.

109
00:07:54,609 --> 00:07:56,511
Check if there’s
an available bed.

110
00:07:57,178 --> 00:08:00,688
I will call Dr. Dumagat to inform
him about the stroke patient.

111
00:08:01,494 --> 00:08:02,508
Ma...

112
00:08:03,302 --> 00:08:05,096
Ma, grandma’s in
the emergency room.

113
00:08:05,721 --> 00:08:07,181
Please call me back.

114
00:08:12,561 --> 00:08:16,383
For now, our priority is to
stabilize your grandmother.

115
00:08:17,811 --> 00:08:20,064
Can you tell us what happened?

116
00:08:20,778 --> 00:08:21,778
Uhm…

117
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:24,255
Doc, we were just at the fair.

118
00:08:25,074 --> 00:08:26,075
Grandma was still strong.

119
00:08:26,075 --> 00:08:27,493
She even played games.

120
00:08:28,599 --> 00:08:29,809
She sat down for a moment ‘cause

121
00:08:29,809 --> 00:08:31,495
we were going on rides.

122
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:33,055
Then when she stood up,

123
00:08:33,059 --> 00:08:34,480
she suddenly got weak.

124
00:08:35,012 --> 00:08:36,808
Then... she fell down.

125
00:08:36,812 --> 00:08:37,868
She collapsed.

126
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:38,892
When she fell, Doc,

127
00:08:38,898 --> 00:08:40,488
we brought her here immediately.

128
00:08:40,512 --> 00:08:42,040
But while on the way, Doc,

129
00:08:42,064 --> 00:08:43,607
she lost consciousness.

130
00:08:45,913 --> 00:08:48,570
It appears that your
grandmother had a stroke.

131
00:08:48,573 --> 00:08:49,722
Stroke?

132
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:52,619
She’s in a critical condition.

133
00:08:52,619 --> 00:08:54,053
She needs to stay in the ICU

134
00:08:54,066 --> 00:08:56,331
to get checked by
several specialists.

135
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,414
Does she have any
advance directives?

136
00:09:02,702 --> 00:09:04,996
What are advance directives?

137
00:09:05,230 --> 00:09:07,733
This is if she has any wishes
not to be intubated

138
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:11,278
or not to receive CPR
if her heart stops.

139
00:09:12,805 --> 00:09:15,058
If you don’t remember anything,

140
00:09:15,058 --> 00:09:17,215
you need to discuss as a family

141
00:09:17,219 --> 00:09:18,846
how aggressive you would be

142
00:09:18,846 --> 00:09:20,518
in your grandmother's treatment.

143
00:09:21,798 --> 00:09:24,175
She could fully recover,

144
00:09:24,175 --> 00:09:26,970
or she might also not be
the same as before

145
00:09:26,970 --> 00:09:29,555
even with all the
necessary treatment.

146
00:09:30,098 --> 00:09:32,183
I’ll leave this
consent form with you.

147
00:09:32,807 --> 00:09:35,663
Whatever decision
you make as a family,

148
00:09:35,687 --> 00:09:36,938
we’ll respect it.

149
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:38,730
I’ll go ahead.

150
00:09:46,531 --> 00:09:48,032
Ma...

151
00:10:40,132 --> 00:10:41,575
Hello?

152
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:42,976
Hello, Blessie?

153
00:10:42,977 --> 00:10:44,477
Hello, Blessie?!

154
00:10:44,894 --> 00:10:45,979
Blessie, my dear.

155
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:47,105
What happened?

156
00:10:47,707 --> 00:10:49,876
Ma, I'm at the hospital
with grandma.

157
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:53,335
They’re running tests on her.

158
00:10:53,913 --> 00:10:54,913
Uhm...

159
00:10:56,026 --> 00:10:59,696
Didn’t I tell you not
to tire your grandma?

160
00:11:00,623 --> 00:11:01,957
Let me talk to her, please.

161
00:11:03,518 --> 00:11:04,894
She might have had a stroke, Ma.

162
00:11:08,632 --> 00:11:09,632
Wha—

163
00:11:09,657 --> 00:11:10,657
What?

164
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:12,209
Stroke?

165
00:11:16,704 --> 00:11:18,372
Can you make it home?

166
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:21,999
Uh. Uhm...

167
00:11:23,827 --> 00:11:24,953
Blessie, uhm…

168
00:11:24,953 --> 00:11:26,579
it’s not that…

169
00:11:26,579 --> 00:11:28,915
it’s not that easy to… uhm...

170
00:11:28,915 --> 00:11:31,191
to file leave at work, but uhm…

171
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:34,337
Yes, of course.
I’ll do everything.

172
00:11:34,337 --> 00:11:36,005
I’ll get home as soon as I can.

173
00:11:37,674 --> 00:11:39,134
How’s grandma?

174
00:11:39,134 --> 00:11:40,488
What did the doctors say?

175
00:11:40,496 --> 00:11:41,816
She’s not awake yet.

176
00:11:42,802 --> 00:11:45,009
So we’re not really sure.

177
00:11:46,915 --> 00:11:49,083
I don’t know what to do.

178
00:11:49,626 --> 00:11:51,002
They’re asking about...

179
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:53,213
advance directives.

180
00:11:53,213 --> 00:11:55,089
Ma, what is this?

181
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:57,800
Don’t panic too much, okay?

182
00:11:58,009 --> 00:11:59,636
Mommy’s right here.

183
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,448
What I’ll do is...

184
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:04,992
is to send you
money immediately.

185
00:12:05,016 --> 00:12:06,900
Just tell me what you need.

186
00:12:07,644 --> 00:12:09,437
Blessie, listen.

187
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:11,189
The most important thing…

188
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:13,566
is that your grandma survives.

189
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:14,566
Okay?

190
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:16,277
Ma...

191
00:12:17,114 --> 00:12:18,407
Please come home.

192
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:20,990
Promise me.

193
00:12:24,494 --> 00:12:25,912
I’ll do everything.

194
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,958
Yes, my dear.
Of course I’ll come home.

195
00:12:32,252 --> 00:12:34,880
But for now, stay strong, okay?

196
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:38,716
I’ll call you after work.

197
00:12:39,217 --> 00:12:40,468
Be strong.

198
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:42,993
Alright.

199
00:13:11,689 --> 00:13:12,899
Grandma…

200
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:15,753
Agatha is waiting for us.

201
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:21,717
Wake up, please.

202
00:13:23,386 --> 00:13:24,720
I promise.

203
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:27,295
We’ll buy you
pancit for long life.

204
00:13:29,994 --> 00:13:32,705
We’re bringing the
dollhouse home too, right?

205
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:35,815
We’ve gone back there
five times already.

206
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:01,924
Grandma…

207
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,603
Mommy will come, okay?

208
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,224
Her flight isn’t scheduled yet,

209
00:14:10,228 --> 00:14:12,356
but she’ll come home.

210
00:14:15,294 --> 00:14:17,023
We still need to clean the house.

211
00:14:17,039 --> 00:14:19,025
Please, don’t leave us.

212
00:14:54,191 --> 00:14:56,985
Ma’am Blessie? Ma’am Blessie.

213
00:14:56,985 --> 00:14:58,236
I'm sorry.

214
00:14:58,236 --> 00:15:00,383
We need to take the stand now.

215
00:15:00,407 --> 00:15:01,448
Yeah, sure.

216
00:15:02,699 --> 00:15:04,576
Thank you. Our condolences.

217
00:15:04,576 --> 00:15:06,078
Thank you.
Have something to eat first.

218
00:15:06,078 --> 00:15:07,579
It’s alright. Thank you.

219
00:15:22,177 --> 00:15:23,637
You can drop them here.

220
00:15:25,087 --> 00:15:26,422
Thank you.

221
00:15:29,893 --> 00:15:32,813
Just here.
That's fine. Thank you.

222
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:35,816
Why did it take you so
long to get here?

223
00:15:36,191 --> 00:15:37,275
You missed it.

224
00:15:37,275 --> 00:15:38,902
Grandma’s already buried.

225
00:15:38,902 --> 00:15:40,862
We’ve been waiting for
you since yesterday.

226
00:15:40,862 --> 00:15:42,906
Blessie...
My dear, I…

227
00:15:42,906 --> 00:15:45,033
I’m sorry, it was just…
it was terrible…

228
00:15:45,033 --> 00:15:48,995
There was a hurricane
and all the flights got cancelled.

229
00:15:48,995 --> 00:15:50,647
Grandma was in the
hospital for two weeks.

230
00:15:51,209 --> 00:15:52,661
She lay in wake for a week too.

231
00:15:54,501 --> 00:15:56,253
I’m really sorry.

232
00:15:56,753 --> 00:15:58,588
I just didn’t expect…

233
00:15:59,631 --> 00:16:01,258
That grandma would die?

234
00:16:03,176 --> 00:16:04,422
Alright. I’ll take a nap.

235
00:16:06,388 --> 00:16:08,306
- Mommy!
- Agatha!

236
00:16:08,306 --> 00:16:09,552
- Hi!
- Wow!

237
00:16:09,766 --> 00:16:11,143
My baby!

238
00:16:11,143 --> 00:16:12,143
Wow!

239
00:16:13,061 --> 00:16:14,771
You’ve grown so much.

240
00:16:14,771 --> 00:16:16,565
You’re so much bigger than…

241
00:16:16,565 --> 00:16:17,774
Oh my gosh.

242
00:16:17,774 --> 00:16:19,526
You really are
prettier in person

243
00:16:19,526 --> 00:16:21,319
than on video call!

244
00:16:22,529 --> 00:16:24,114
I missed you, my baby.

245
00:16:37,712 --> 00:16:39,171
By the way, Grandma,

246
00:16:39,808 --> 00:16:41,476
your daughter is back.

247
00:16:42,203 --> 00:16:43,454
You know…

248
00:16:44,092 --> 00:16:46,762
If she had come
just two hours earlier,

249
00:16:47,512 --> 00:16:49,431
she would have made it.

250
00:16:49,431 --> 00:16:50,640
What a shame.

251
00:16:53,602 --> 00:16:55,395
When you were in the hospital,

252
00:16:56,188 --> 00:16:57,815
could you still hear me then?

253
00:16:59,608 --> 00:17:00,860
Because…

254
00:17:01,443 --> 00:17:03,278
I talked to you every day.

255
00:17:03,278 --> 00:17:04,488
Then…

256
00:17:05,363 --> 00:17:07,616
Agatha recorded her stories

257
00:17:07,616 --> 00:17:09,826
so you wouldn’t get bored.

258
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:13,491
How about now, Grandma?

259
00:17:13,515 --> 00:17:15,207
Can you still hear me?

260
00:17:15,749 --> 00:17:17,000
Grandma...

261
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,376
I’m checking your cards.

262
00:17:19,795 --> 00:17:22,005
Oh, you have so many pairs.

263
00:17:22,005 --> 00:17:24,174
You might still beat me.

264
00:17:24,174 --> 00:17:26,176
I don’t want to play anymore.

265
00:17:26,804 --> 00:17:28,848
Your cards are better, anyway.

266
00:17:36,025 --> 00:17:37,285
At least with you, Grandma...

267
00:17:38,179 --> 00:17:40,348
you took care of me and Agatha.

268
00:17:43,276 --> 00:17:45,237
You never left us when…

269
00:17:45,237 --> 00:17:47,531
when mommy went abroad,

270
00:17:48,406 --> 00:17:50,617
or when she and daddy separated.

271
00:17:53,503 --> 00:17:55,491
You gave your very best for us.

272
00:17:59,039 --> 00:18:00,790
Even though we weren’t
your responsibility,

273
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,834
you raised us as if you
were our real mom.

274
00:18:12,146 --> 00:18:13,481
Ma’am Blessie?

275
00:18:13,981 --> 00:18:15,483
- Yes?
- Delivery for you.

276
00:18:15,483 --> 00:18:16,483
Right here.

277
00:18:17,777 --> 00:18:18,903
Delivery.

278
00:18:18,903 --> 00:18:20,863
- Thank you. Take care.
- Thank you.

279
00:18:21,489 --> 00:18:22,782
What did I order again?

280
00:18:27,078 --> 00:18:28,496
Finally.

281
00:18:29,705 --> 00:18:31,415
Mommy, should I put the
water spinach in?

282
00:18:31,916 --> 00:18:33,501
Baby, don’t worry.
I’ll do it, okay?

283
00:18:33,501 --> 00:18:35,503
Hmm… I'm a good cook.

284
00:18:35,503 --> 00:18:37,630
I even cooked for
Blessie and grandma.

285
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:38,923
I’ll put these in.

286
00:18:38,923 --> 00:18:40,216
Yes, I know.

287
00:18:40,216 --> 00:18:41,638
But I’m already here.

288
00:18:41,652 --> 00:18:43,685
And remember,
you’re still my baby.

289
00:18:43,685 --> 00:18:45,693
So now, I’ll do the cooking,

290
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:46,993
and you’ll be the one eating.

291
00:18:47,007 --> 00:18:48,342
- You and your sister, okay?
- Okay.

292
00:18:48,342 --> 00:18:49,635
- Okay.
- Okay, sit down first.

293
00:18:49,635 --> 00:18:50,761
Alright then.

294
00:18:50,761 --> 00:18:52,220
It’ll be ready in just a moment.

295
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:53,805
Wow, chicken!

296
00:18:53,805 --> 00:18:55,557
- Can I have some?
- Hmmm…

297
00:18:55,557 --> 00:18:56,558
- Do you want some?
- Yeah.

298
00:18:56,558 --> 00:18:58,784
- Go on. Take one.
- Give me.

299
00:18:58,798 --> 00:19:01,683
Blessie, wash your hands
first before eating.

300
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,966
Salmon sinigang.

301
00:19:05,359 --> 00:19:06,860
Here you go.

302
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:10,113
Baby, you should eat vegetables.

303
00:19:10,113 --> 00:19:11,615
You can’t eat just junk.

304
00:19:11,615 --> 00:19:13,659
Because when you eat vegetables,

305
00:19:13,659 --> 00:19:17,037
you know, you’re gonna grow
taller and smarter.

306
00:19:17,037 --> 00:19:18,246
Is that fish?

307
00:19:18,246 --> 00:19:19,957
Yes. Fish.

308
00:19:19,957 --> 00:19:21,792
You know, this was your
sister’s favorite

309
00:19:21,792 --> 00:19:23,627
when she was a baby.

310
00:19:23,627 --> 00:19:25,212
Remember, Blessie?

311
00:19:25,212 --> 00:19:27,547
You know, my student Morgan?

312
00:19:28,131 --> 00:19:30,300
He's really smart because

313
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,761
he eats lots of vegetables.

314
00:19:32,761 --> 00:19:34,888
He’ll be an astronaut soon.

315
00:19:34,888 --> 00:19:36,884
You want to be
an astronaut, right?

316
00:19:36,891 --> 00:19:38,309
I don’t want that anymore.

317
00:19:38,316 --> 00:19:41,277
Actually, I want to be
a doctor now, mommy.

318
00:19:41,277 --> 00:19:43,571
Uhm… be a brain surgeon.

319
00:19:43,571 --> 00:19:44,739
Wow. Really?

320
00:19:44,739 --> 00:19:45,990
- That's nice.
- Yeah.

321
00:19:45,990 --> 00:19:47,496
If you study in the UK,

322
00:19:47,499 --> 00:19:50,335
there are a lot of opportunities.

323
00:19:50,335 --> 00:19:52,838
Lots of schools give scholarships

324
00:19:52,838 --> 00:19:55,110
for healthcare workers.

325
00:19:55,122 --> 00:19:57,083
Because they’re in demand there.

326
00:19:57,083 --> 00:19:58,125
Really?

327
00:19:58,125 --> 00:19:59,710
Yes, baby. Here.

328
00:19:59,710 --> 00:20:01,003
Eat first.

329
00:20:01,671 --> 00:20:03,422
This is Blessie’s,

330
00:20:03,422 --> 00:20:05,049
then yours.

331
00:20:09,553 --> 00:20:11,055
- Mommy?
- Hmm?

332
00:20:11,055 --> 00:20:13,808
Is it okay if you move
to the other chair?

333
00:20:15,726 --> 00:20:17,061
Yeah. Of course.

334
00:20:17,061 --> 00:20:19,480
Sorry, but it's grandma's seat.

335
00:20:19,939 --> 00:20:21,857
- No problem.
- Sorry, Ma.

336
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:23,543
It’s okay.

337
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:25,361
Can you eat by yourself?

338
00:20:25,653 --> 00:20:27,113
You’re a big girl now, right?

339
00:20:29,073 --> 00:20:31,867
Can Blessie study in the UK too?

340
00:20:34,328 --> 00:20:36,372
Well, your sister is...

341
00:20:36,372 --> 00:20:38,332
over 18 years old now.

342
00:20:38,332 --> 00:20:42,294
So processing her papers
is a bit tricky.

343
00:20:42,294 --> 00:20:44,964
I think… it might be more difficult.

344
00:20:44,964 --> 00:20:47,967
Maybe there’s another way
for us to go together?

345
00:20:48,801 --> 00:20:50,261
What are you talking about, Agatha?

346
00:20:50,261 --> 00:20:52,054
I don't even want to go there.

347
00:20:52,722 --> 00:20:53,722
Here.

348
00:20:53,723 --> 00:20:55,850
Eat this salmon.
You talk too much.

349
00:20:55,850 --> 00:20:57,268
- I don’t want salmon.
- There, there you go.

350
00:20:57,268 --> 00:20:59,311
- You know I don’t like salmon.
- Don’t play with your food, okay?

351
00:20:59,311 --> 00:21:00,479
- You might spill it.
- There you go.

352
00:21:00,479 --> 00:21:01,897
- I worked hard for that.
- I don’t want that.

353
00:21:01,897 --> 00:21:03,566
- Oh, no!
- I told you!

354
00:21:05,088 --> 00:21:08,403
I said if you don’t want to eat it,
then don't play with it.

355
00:21:08,428 --> 00:21:10,102
You just made a mess.

356
00:21:19,206 --> 00:21:21,917
How do we do this?
It looks all messy.

357
00:21:23,377 --> 00:21:25,421
- That’s not the one for the beak.
- Wow, orange!

358
00:21:25,421 --> 00:21:26,505
- Which one?
- Pass me the other one.

359
00:21:26,505 --> 00:21:27,798
- This?
- Yes. Give it to me.

360
00:21:27,798 --> 00:21:29,133
- Here, okay.
- Let me see.

361
00:21:29,133 --> 00:21:31,802
That one’s nice.
This one’s ugly. Look.

362
00:21:31,802 --> 00:21:33,262
Where’s the glue gun, anyway?

363
00:21:33,262 --> 00:21:34,597
I don’t know.

364
00:21:34,597 --> 00:21:36,390
Wait, I’ll get it first.

365
00:21:37,391 --> 00:21:38,684
Oh, Blessie…

366
00:21:39,306 --> 00:21:41,433
Baby… Agatha, I'm sorry.

367
00:21:41,896 --> 00:21:44,023
Mommy snapped earlier.

368
00:21:44,023 --> 00:21:45,691
It’s because you were
playing with your food.

369
00:21:45,691 --> 00:21:47,735
That’s a blessing from God.

370
00:21:47,997 --> 00:21:49,624
Sorry, mommy.

371
00:21:50,112 --> 00:21:51,280
It’s okay.

372
00:21:51,697 --> 00:21:53,657
You know that balikbayan box?

373
00:21:53,657 --> 00:21:55,242
Mommy brought a lot of gifts.

374
00:21:55,242 --> 00:21:57,286
Blessie, help. It’s heavy.

375
00:21:57,286 --> 00:21:59,121
- Blessie?
- I’ll do it, mommy.

376
00:21:59,121 --> 00:22:00,998
Okay, sure. Help me.

377
00:22:02,708 --> 00:22:04,877
- Look, I have some surprises in there.
- Woah!

378
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:06,462
Oh, baby!

379
00:22:06,462 --> 00:22:07,922
This one. London.

380
00:22:07,922 --> 00:22:09,508
- Look, Blessie.
- London?

381
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:12,706
It doesn’t fit me.

382
00:22:14,428 --> 00:22:16,514
Ah, never mind.
We’ll just buy again.

383
00:22:16,514 --> 00:22:18,891
- Okay.
- Oh, this is for you, Blessie.

384
00:22:18,891 --> 00:22:20,893
That’s yours so you can match.

385
00:22:20,893 --> 00:22:22,019
- You can have this instead.
- We’ll just make a…

386
00:22:22,019 --> 00:22:23,105
Thank you! Mommy,

387
00:22:23,112 --> 00:22:25,862
just buy her one when
you go back to the UK.

388
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:27,365
Of course.

389
00:22:27,372 --> 00:22:29,791
Woah! This is grandma’s favorite.

390
00:22:30,546 --> 00:22:32,006
Yes, that’s her favorite.

391
00:22:32,006 --> 00:22:34,509
You know, I was going
to fill this box.

392
00:22:34,509 --> 00:22:37,345
But it was sudden.
There was no time.

393
00:22:37,345 --> 00:22:40,348
But I have a surprise...

394
00:22:40,973 --> 00:22:42,767
Surprise!

395
00:22:43,351 --> 00:22:44,936
- Okay.
- Just the two of us then.

396
00:22:44,936 --> 00:22:47,396
- One. Two. Three.
- Oh my god. It’s so pretty.

397
00:22:47,396 --> 00:22:49,190
Wow!

398
00:22:49,190 --> 00:22:52,026
- It’s so pretty!
- See?

399
00:22:52,485 --> 00:22:54,582
- Sis, look at this!
- Look, it has furniture.

400
00:22:54,607 --> 00:22:55,607
- Go on.
- Sis, look!

401
00:22:55,632 --> 00:22:58,010
- Oh, it's here.
- You know who bought this?

402
00:22:58,501 --> 00:23:00,753
Uncle Neville.

403
00:23:01,077 --> 00:23:02,524
So you had time to go
shopping with your boyfriend

404
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:03,925
before you went home, huh.

405
00:23:04,361 --> 00:23:06,738
Sis, help me put the furniture in.

406
00:23:06,738 --> 00:23:08,574
Look, this is so cool. It’s so pretty.

407
00:23:08,574 --> 00:23:11,118
This goes in the kitchen.
Where’s the kitchen?

408
00:23:12,578 --> 00:23:15,455
The toilet... where’s the bathroom?

409
00:23:20,085 --> 00:23:21,545
Agatha!

410
00:23:22,254 --> 00:23:24,840
You took my soap again, didn’t you?

411
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:26,842
What soap?

412
00:23:26,842 --> 00:23:28,343
The White Rose Papaya.

413
00:23:28,343 --> 00:23:29,887
I just opened that.

414
00:23:30,179 --> 00:23:32,598
Not me. Maybe it’s mommy.

415
00:23:36,977 --> 00:23:39,688
She just got here, and she's
already messing with everything.

416
00:23:46,820 --> 00:23:50,240
Here you go. Try this soap.

417
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:52,159
It will make you pretty.

418
00:23:52,159 --> 00:23:54,912
Don’t you think your
granddaughter’s pretty?

419
00:23:54,912 --> 00:23:57,122
It makes your skin pretty and smooth.

420
00:23:57,122 --> 00:23:59,875
You didn’t let me finish, my dear.

421
00:24:00,584 --> 00:24:02,232
You’re the best, Grandma.

422
00:24:40,165 --> 00:24:41,166
[clears throat]

423
00:24:46,380 --> 00:24:47,506
Blessie.

424
00:24:48,548 --> 00:24:50,259
You’re still up?

425
00:24:52,219 --> 00:24:54,137
Don’t you have an early

426
00:24:54,137 --> 00:24:56,056
shift at the café tomorrow?

427
00:24:59,351 --> 00:25:01,061
I don’t have a job anymore.

428
00:25:01,853 --> 00:25:03,522
They let me go...

429
00:25:03,939 --> 00:25:05,440
after I missed so many days

430
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:07,192
when grandma
was in the hospital.

431
00:25:10,779 --> 00:25:12,572
That’s so unfair.

432
00:25:12,572 --> 00:25:14,449
They had no consideration at all.

433
00:25:16,076 --> 00:25:18,578
This one’s good—
why don't you eat this?

434
00:25:22,541 --> 00:25:24,084
It’s already expired.

435
00:25:24,084 --> 00:25:26,128
Good thing I brought two more.

436
00:25:26,128 --> 00:25:27,587
They’re really good.

437
00:25:27,587 --> 00:25:29,464
Only grandma eats those.

438
00:25:30,132 --> 00:25:33,051
We’re not really
into butter cookies.

439
00:25:34,219 --> 00:25:37,681
Alright then, I’ll just give
them to the neighbors.

440
00:26:00,746 --> 00:26:01,913
Blessie…

441
00:26:03,957 --> 00:26:05,876
Is there still room for me?

442
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:10,589
Isn’t the living room
more spacious?

443
00:26:11,631 --> 00:26:13,383
Uh, yeah, but…

444
00:26:13,383 --> 00:26:14,509
uhm...

445
00:26:15,677 --> 00:26:17,427
It’s just… there’s air conditioning here,

446
00:26:17,451 --> 00:26:18,910
and a lot of mosquitoes out there.

447
00:26:19,577 --> 00:26:22,664
Even grandma used to sleep here.

448
00:26:22,895 --> 00:26:24,563
I’ll just squeeze in.

449
00:27:08,251 --> 00:27:10,628
Sis, we’re up next.

450
00:27:10,628 --> 00:27:12,630
It’s okay. We can do this.

451
00:27:12,630 --> 00:27:14,507
We practiced this last week, right?

452
00:27:14,507 --> 00:27:16,217
- Yeah.
- Our next performer...

453
00:27:16,217 --> 00:27:17,719
from Grade 4, Section 1—

454
00:27:17,719 --> 00:27:19,220
Agatha Ronquillo.

455
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:22,432
[applause]

456
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:25,101
Excuse me.

457
00:27:28,105 --> 00:27:30,649
In a faraway mountain,

458
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:32,443
there was a mother bird

459
00:27:32,443 --> 00:27:34,111
who kept flying and flying

460
00:27:34,111 --> 00:27:37,865
to look for food for her chick.

461
00:27:37,865 --> 00:27:40,325
After searching for so long,

462
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:43,370
she only found a single worm.

463
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:44,663
Twit-twit.

464
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:47,082
Oh no… what do I do?

465
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:49,710
This isn’t enough for me and my baby.

466
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:50,710
Twit-twit.

467
00:27:51,086 --> 00:27:54,423
Twit-twit. Mom, I’m hungry.

468
00:27:54,935 --> 00:27:58,731
Twit-twit.
Yes, baby. Here’s your food.

469
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:03,599
What about you?
What will you eat?

470
00:28:04,183 --> 00:28:08,437
Uh, I’ll fly out to find some, okay?

471
00:28:08,437 --> 00:28:11,190
Twit-twit.
Come back soon, Mom.

472
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:12,691
Yes, baby.

473
00:28:15,569 --> 00:28:19,281
And the mother bird flew far away.

474
00:28:19,281 --> 00:28:20,532
When she returned,

475
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:23,368
she brought more worms.

476
00:28:23,744 --> 00:28:26,288
Yay! I’m bigger now!

477
00:28:26,288 --> 00:28:28,790
Twit-twit.
Here are your worms, baby.

478
00:28:28,790 --> 00:28:29,790
Twit-twit.

479
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:32,995
Wow! My baby’s so big now…

480
00:28:33,019 --> 00:28:35,255
but you’re still my baby, okay?

481
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:37,674
The little bird was so happy

482
00:28:37,674 --> 00:28:40,052
when the mother bird came back.

483
00:28:40,052 --> 00:28:42,804
But she has a surprise—

484
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:45,182
she’s going to have a sibling.

485
00:28:48,467 --> 00:28:51,804
Yuck, sis, you sound like
you’re pooping.

486
00:28:53,106 --> 00:28:54,441
But it’s true.

487
00:28:56,068 --> 00:28:58,695
But what the two
didn’t expect was

488
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:01,323
that their mother bird would
never come home.

489
00:29:02,282 --> 00:29:06,125
Worms would appear
every time they woke up,

490
00:29:06,149 --> 00:29:08,288
but their mother wasn’t there.

491
00:29:09,352 --> 00:29:13,273
So the two siblings learned to fly

492
00:29:13,273 --> 00:29:16,391
as they searched for their mother.

493
00:29:16,776 --> 00:29:19,529
They also started finding ways

494
00:29:19,529 --> 00:29:21,197
to improve their nest.

495
00:29:21,197 --> 00:29:23,533
As time passed,

496
00:29:23,533 --> 00:29:27,808
their nest became more
and more beautiful.

497
00:29:28,204 --> 00:29:30,039
The two of them stayed together—

498
00:29:30,039 --> 00:29:33,293
facing problems and
storms side by side.

499
00:29:34,252 --> 00:29:37,714
They dreamed and
hoped that one day,

500
00:29:37,714 --> 00:29:41,926
their mother would
see their beautiful nest.

501
00:29:41,926 --> 00:29:44,345
They remembered their mother,

502
00:29:44,345 --> 00:29:48,183
wherever the wind had carried her.

503
00:29:48,183 --> 00:29:49,350
[audience whispering]
Did the mother bird die?

504
00:29:49,350 --> 00:29:51,561
[audience whispering]
She’s dead?

505
00:29:52,395 --> 00:29:53,897
Oh… what happened?

506
00:29:58,417 --> 00:30:00,753
[applause]

507
00:30:15,112 --> 00:30:16,155
Blessie…

508
00:30:16,592 --> 00:30:18,177
Have a snack.

509
00:30:30,191 --> 00:30:33,153
Why did that happen
at your sister’s school?

510
00:30:34,608 --> 00:30:36,026
What’s wrong?

511
00:30:36,321 --> 00:30:38,094
Why did the mother bird die?

512
00:30:38,798 --> 00:30:41,217
I don’t know.
Why don’t you ask her?

513
00:30:42,660 --> 00:30:45,203
You’re treating
our lives like a joke.

514
00:30:45,705 --> 00:30:47,832
No mother wants to be separated

515
00:30:47,832 --> 00:30:49,472
or be away from her children.

516
00:30:50,460 --> 00:30:52,013
Nobody was laughing earlier.

517
00:30:52,378 --> 00:30:54,102
And not everything is about you.

518
00:30:54,631 --> 00:30:56,479
If you have a problem with me,

519
00:30:56,966 --> 00:30:58,343
don’t drag your sister into it!

520
00:30:58,343 --> 00:31:00,178
Don’t poison her mind

521
00:31:00,178 --> 00:31:02,068
like whatever poison is in yours!

522
00:31:04,599 --> 00:31:05,808
Really?

523
00:31:06,726 --> 00:31:08,561
You’re blaming me for that, too?

524
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:10,243
Agatha’s grown now.

525
00:31:10,897 --> 00:31:12,120
She’s almost in high school.

526
00:31:12,607 --> 00:31:13,900
She knows you
don’t have time for us.

527
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:15,610
I don’t even know
why you came home.

528
00:31:18,905 --> 00:31:20,823
I had to stay there…

529
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,408
because what?

530
00:31:22,408 --> 00:31:23,409
Our house was hit by a storm,

531
00:31:23,409 --> 00:31:24,952
it was infested with termites.

532
00:31:24,952 --> 00:31:26,759
I had to take care
of your sister’s health.

533
00:31:27,163 --> 00:31:28,498
Your sister got sick.

534
00:31:28,498 --> 00:31:30,104
I had to go back to the UK!

535
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,502
I did everything!

536
00:31:32,835 --> 00:31:33,920
What about you?

537
00:31:35,171 --> 00:31:37,090
All you had to do
was do well at school—

538
00:31:37,090 --> 00:31:38,549
and you still didn’t.

539
00:31:38,549 --> 00:31:39,759
You would’ve finished
nursing by now…

540
00:31:39,759 --> 00:31:41,232
You could’ve already been in the UK.

541
00:31:42,804 --> 00:31:44,055
Nothing I can do.

542
00:31:44,055 --> 00:31:45,278
I'm dumb.

543
00:31:45,807 --> 00:31:46,988
Sorry, I’m not perfect.

544
00:31:47,392 --> 00:31:48,698
Don’t worry about me.

545
00:31:50,269 --> 00:31:51,784
I didn't say you’re dumb, Blessie.

546
00:31:54,607 --> 00:31:55,997
Yeah, you don’t say it…

547
00:31:56,901 --> 00:31:59,083
But you always make me feel
that I’m not enough.

548
00:31:59,987 --> 00:32:01,948
You know, next thing,
you’re going to

549
00:32:01,948 --> 00:32:03,171
blame me for being born.

550
00:32:03,491 --> 00:32:05,201
Because I wasn’t part
of the plan, right?

551
00:32:05,201 --> 00:32:06,201
Yes!

552
00:32:06,494 --> 00:32:08,301
You weren’t part of the plan!

553
00:32:09,455 --> 00:32:10,637
But what else can I do?

554
00:32:11,374 --> 00:32:13,348
I made you my life.

555
00:32:14,627 --> 00:32:16,684
Look! I’m giving you a good life.

556
00:32:17,088 --> 00:32:18,089
Here it is!

557
00:32:18,089 --> 00:32:19,132
It’s right in front of you!

558
00:32:19,132 --> 00:32:21,050
Far from the life here
in the Philippines.

559
00:32:21,050 --> 00:32:22,607
We can feel how far it is.

560
00:32:23,261 --> 00:32:25,360
We really feel how
far away you are.

561
00:32:27,181 --> 00:32:28,433
Hi!

562
00:32:29,016 --> 00:32:30,768
Hi, Mommy. Hi, Sis.

563
00:32:31,185 --> 00:32:33,229
Look, guys! It’s so pretty.

564
00:32:33,229 --> 00:32:35,328
It’s just tight… I can’t zip it.

565
00:32:35,773 --> 00:32:38,568
- It doesn’t fit?
- Yeah, it won’t close.

566
00:32:38,568 --> 00:32:40,027
It's pretty.

567
00:32:40,027 --> 00:32:41,988
It would’ve fit you three years ago.

568
00:32:41,988 --> 00:32:43,573
It doesn’t fit.

569
00:32:43,573 --> 00:32:46,576
You’re such a downer.
You’re always picking on Mommy.

570
00:32:46,576 --> 00:32:48,244
I’m just saying the truth.

571
00:32:48,244 --> 00:32:50,747
Never mind.
I’ll buy you a new one, okay?

572
00:32:50,747 --> 00:32:52,540
So you can be a flower girl.

573
00:32:53,249 --> 00:32:54,459
A flower girl?

574
00:32:54,917 --> 00:32:56,891
Agatha’s all grown up to be a flower girl.

575
00:33:01,007 --> 00:33:02,467
How about you, Blessie?

576
00:33:03,134 --> 00:33:04,607
You want to be a flower girl too?

577
00:33:04,969 --> 00:33:06,651
Isn’t it your dream—
to be a flower girl?

578
00:33:07,555 --> 00:33:08,736
There’s still time!

579
00:33:09,682 --> 00:33:10,683
What’s the hype?

580
00:33:10,683 --> 00:33:12,059
Who’s getting married?

581
00:33:13,144 --> 00:33:14,270
Me.

582
00:33:15,146 --> 00:33:16,814
Your Uncle Neville and I.

583
00:33:19,192 --> 00:33:20,331
Oh, is that so?

584
00:33:21,778 --> 00:33:23,084
Best wishes, then!

585
00:33:23,946 --> 00:33:25,295
Congratulations!

586
00:33:33,706 --> 00:33:36,584
Mom’s been to a lot
of places, huh, Pa?

587
00:33:38,336 --> 00:33:40,129
You’re such a disrespectful brat!

588
00:33:40,129 --> 00:33:41,129
Argh!

589
00:33:41,154 --> 00:33:42,298
Why?!

590
00:33:42,632 --> 00:33:43,633
Why did you even come back

591
00:33:43,633 --> 00:33:45,092
when life already seemed
very happy for you?!

592
00:33:45,092 --> 00:33:47,678
You even have the nerve
to say this is all for us!

593
00:33:47,678 --> 00:33:50,181
But you only came home
to invite us to your wedding?

594
00:33:50,181 --> 00:33:52,405
What? So you can look
like a good mother?

595
00:33:54,101 --> 00:33:55,102
Grandma already died,

596
00:33:55,102 --> 00:33:56,437
and it took you so
long to come home

597
00:33:56,437 --> 00:33:58,356
because you were so happy there!

598
00:33:58,689 --> 00:34:00,858
The way you talk,

599
00:34:00,858 --> 00:34:02,777
you make it sound like
it’s just a jeepney ride

600
00:34:02,777 --> 00:34:04,737
from the UK to the Philippines.

601
00:34:06,603 --> 00:34:09,111
I wasn’t able to take care
of my own sick mother

602
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:11,508
while she was in the hospital, dying!

603
00:34:12,324 --> 00:34:14,368
Because I had to work—for her,

604
00:34:14,368 --> 00:34:16,829
for her hospital bills, for you!

605
00:34:17,287 --> 00:34:19,331
But did you wait for me?

606
00:34:19,873 --> 00:34:21,834
Did you wait for me?
You knew I was on my way,

607
00:34:21,834 --> 00:34:23,919
but you didn’t wait
for me for the funeral!

608
00:34:23,919 --> 00:34:25,295
Wait?!

609
00:34:25,796 --> 00:34:28,507
Grandma died waiting for you!

610
00:34:28,815 --> 00:34:30,358
How dare you!

611
00:34:32,427 --> 00:34:34,572
You are so ungrateful!

612
00:34:35,097 --> 00:34:36,723
Do you even know how much

613
00:34:36,723 --> 00:34:38,243
teachers earn here
in the Philippines?

614
00:34:38,559 --> 00:34:41,019
Because if teachers
were paid well here,

615
00:34:41,019 --> 00:34:44,314
I wouldn’t have had to go
to the UK and work there

616
00:34:44,314 --> 00:34:46,400
just to provide
for the two of you!

617
00:34:48,277 --> 00:34:49,671
How many Christmases…

618
00:34:50,195 --> 00:34:51,548
how many birthdays…

619
00:34:52,364 --> 00:34:54,324
how many special
occasions, Blessie...

620
00:34:54,324 --> 00:34:57,953
I endured not being with you.

621
00:34:59,580 --> 00:35:03,041
Huh? While your father was
just there in the next barangay!

622
00:35:03,041 --> 00:35:05,627
He couldn’t even be bothered
to check on you—and me?

623
00:35:05,627 --> 00:35:07,713
I’m the bad one? Hmm?

624
00:35:08,255 --> 00:35:10,775
You can’t even video
call me, can you?

625
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:12,926
You don’t even
want to talk to me.

626
00:35:12,926 --> 00:35:14,678
Are you ashamed of me? Huh?

627
00:35:14,678 --> 00:35:16,263
Don’t you care about me?

628
00:35:16,263 --> 00:35:18,640
Your own mother.
Whether I’m alive or dead?!

629
00:35:19,308 --> 00:35:20,308
You know what,

630
00:35:20,642 --> 00:35:22,561
I don’t have time
for your drama.

631
00:35:22,769 --> 00:35:24,456
You really are ungrateful!

632
00:35:25,022 --> 00:35:27,065
That! What you’re wearing,

633
00:35:27,065 --> 00:35:30,277
your phone, that TV— all of it!

634
00:35:30,277 --> 00:35:31,528
Even your life!

635
00:35:31,528 --> 00:35:33,363
You’d have none
of it if not for me!

636
00:35:33,363 --> 00:35:34,865
You wouldn’t even
be in this world

637
00:35:34,865 --> 00:35:36,909
if it weren’t for me—your mother!

638
00:35:36,909 --> 00:35:37,951
Because of you?

639
00:35:37,951 --> 00:35:39,494
Fine, there! It’s yours!

640
00:35:39,494 --> 00:35:41,204
It's yours!
Take it all!

641
00:35:41,204 --> 00:35:43,123
It's yours! Everything is yours!

642
00:35:43,123 --> 00:35:44,666
This? It’s yours!

643
00:35:44,666 --> 00:35:46,501
Here! Take it!

644
00:35:46,501 --> 00:35:49,004
Argh! Take that!
Is that what you want?!

645
00:35:49,004 --> 00:35:50,464
Fine, take it all!

646
00:35:50,464 --> 00:35:52,633
There! Choke on it!

647
00:35:52,633 --> 00:35:54,051
This dollhouse?

648
00:35:54,051 --> 00:35:55,427
Take it back to the UK!

649
00:35:55,427 --> 00:35:57,346
Because we’re too grown up now

650
00:35:57,346 --> 00:35:58,889
to play house with you!

651
00:35:58,889 --> 00:36:00,307
Argh!

652
00:36:08,231 --> 00:36:09,316
Wow!

653
00:36:09,316 --> 00:36:10,442
So, what’s this?

654
00:36:10,442 --> 00:36:12,402
Mommy asked me to tidy up.

655
00:36:12,402 --> 00:36:14,404
She said to choose what to keep.

656
00:36:14,404 --> 00:36:17,074
She’s going to have
the rooms renovated.

657
00:36:17,074 --> 00:36:18,116
The other room’s for us,

658
00:36:18,116 --> 00:36:20,243
and this one’s for her
and Uncle Neville.

659
00:36:21,662 --> 00:36:23,413
Baby, let’s go.

660
00:36:23,413 --> 00:36:24,641
Let’s have dinner outside.

661
00:36:25,165 --> 00:36:26,333
Agatha.

662
00:36:26,333 --> 00:36:27,709
Help me fix Grandma’s things.

663
00:36:27,709 --> 00:36:29,020
There's a busybody around.

664
00:36:29,544 --> 00:36:30,772
Let’s go to the kitchen.

665
00:36:31,421 --> 00:36:32,565
Let her go.

666
00:36:32,965 --> 00:36:34,508
You’re hurting your baby.

667
00:36:34,508 --> 00:36:35,676
Ma...

668
00:36:38,095 --> 00:36:40,156
Are you really taking even
Grandma’s room?

669
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:42,808
Why?

670
00:36:43,642 --> 00:36:45,978
We all know you’ve been
itching to leave anyway,

671
00:36:45,978 --> 00:36:47,956
because you think that
Philippines is hell!

672
00:36:48,522 --> 00:36:50,357
There’s nothing you can do

673
00:36:50,357 --> 00:36:52,567
because this is my house.

674
00:36:52,567 --> 00:36:54,569
Ah… your house?

675
00:36:55,362 --> 00:36:56,780
Fine, then it’s yours!

676
00:36:56,780 --> 00:36:58,323
It hasn’t even been a week
since Grandma’s funeral,

677
00:36:58,323 --> 00:37:00,385
and you’re already excited
to mess up her house.

678
00:37:01,798 --> 00:37:03,508
Maybe you’ve forgotten...

679
00:37:03,996 --> 00:37:06,039
she never asked for any of this.

680
00:37:06,832 --> 00:37:08,166
All Grandma wanted

681
00:37:08,166 --> 00:37:09,459
was for you to come home.

682
00:37:09,459 --> 00:37:11,920
For you to come home
once in a while!

683
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:14,131
If you hadn’t spent so much

684
00:37:14,131 --> 00:37:15,424
and played at the fair too much,

685
00:37:15,424 --> 00:37:17,592
then I could’ve come
home more often, right?

686
00:37:17,592 --> 00:37:20,178
[sarcastic laugh]
Ha! Wow!

687
00:37:21,138 --> 00:37:23,390
You’re even bringing up the fair?

688
00:37:23,390 --> 00:37:25,827
We were already being
careful with money!

689
00:37:26,184 --> 00:37:27,662
The money we spent at the fair?

690
00:37:27,686 --> 00:37:29,622
That you’re holding
a grudge over?

691
00:37:30,397 --> 00:37:33,025
That was our money!
I worked for it!

692
00:37:33,025 --> 00:37:35,193
If you hadn’t skimped on your
Grandma’s hospital care,

693
00:37:35,193 --> 00:37:36,737
she would still be alive!

694
00:37:36,737 --> 00:37:38,447
Maybe I could’ve seen her alive!

695
00:37:38,447 --> 00:37:39,740
What was the point?!

696
00:37:40,407 --> 00:37:41,407
Huh?!

697
00:37:41,742 --> 00:37:43,535
So you could use the
hospital bills as an excuse

698
00:37:43,535 --> 00:37:45,180
to stay longer in London?

699
00:37:46,163 --> 00:37:47,456
Do you think your
money is enough

700
00:37:47,456 --> 00:37:49,207
to make you a good daughter?

701
00:37:50,208 --> 00:37:52,252
Grandma was already exhausted.

702
00:37:52,711 --> 00:37:55,088
She was very exhausted because
you dumped onto her…

703
00:37:55,088 --> 00:37:57,674
and onto me, the duties of
being a mother!

704
00:37:57,674 --> 00:37:59,485
Argh! What do you want?!

705
00:38:01,304 --> 00:38:03,140
Of course, you’ve done
nothing wrong.

706
00:38:03,140 --> 00:38:04,391
You’re innocent.

707
00:38:04,391 --> 00:38:06,435
You’ve done nothing wrong!
Nothing!

708
00:38:06,977 --> 00:38:10,313
The problem with you is you
don't listen anymore!

709
00:38:11,023 --> 00:38:12,582
Do you really think that...

710
00:38:14,151 --> 00:38:16,611
I would put money ahead
of my mother’s life?

711
00:38:16,611 --> 00:38:19,448
I’ve never neglected Grandma.

712
00:38:20,657 --> 00:38:22,300
You’re the only one thinking that way.

713
00:38:23,035 --> 00:38:24,202
I just went along with it

714
00:38:24,202 --> 00:38:25,996
because I knew that’s what
you wanted to think

715
00:38:25,996 --> 00:38:27,956
to forgive yourself

716
00:38:27,956 --> 00:38:29,291
for not being here.

717
00:38:29,291 --> 00:38:31,043
That you're not here
in the Philippines.

718
00:38:31,043 --> 00:38:32,586
What now?

719
00:38:32,586 --> 00:38:35,005
Are you going to slap
me again, Mommy?

720
00:38:38,008 --> 00:38:39,206
Mommy?

721
00:38:41,100 --> 00:38:43,644
Mommy? Blessie, huh?

722
00:38:44,056 --> 00:38:46,433
I’ve been here for a week.

723
00:38:46,933 --> 00:38:48,643
This is the only time
you called me "Mommy".

724
00:38:48,643 --> 00:38:49,770
Did you know that?

725
00:38:49,770 --> 00:38:51,563
Did you even realize that?

726
00:38:52,147 --> 00:38:53,774
Well, I’m not used to it.

727
00:38:54,619 --> 00:38:56,704
I’m not used to having a mother.

728
00:38:57,194 --> 00:38:59,170
You’re so proud to be a teacher…

729
00:39:00,989 --> 00:39:03,158
but you left when
I was still a baby.

730
00:39:03,158 --> 00:39:05,551
You didn’t even teach me
how to count 1, 2, 3.

731
00:39:06,995 --> 00:39:09,748
You’re making excuses about
building a house,

732
00:39:10,290 --> 00:39:13,043
so you have to keep extending
your stay in London.

733
00:39:13,043 --> 00:39:15,170
Even the exterior of the house
has already been tiled,

734
00:39:15,170 --> 00:39:17,063
yet you’re the only one who
hasn’t come home!

735
00:39:17,756 --> 00:39:18,965
Baby?

736
00:39:19,388 --> 00:39:21,223
Sweetheart, come here to mommy.

737
00:39:22,177 --> 00:39:23,512
Baby, I’m sorry, okay?

738
00:39:23,512 --> 00:39:25,472
Your sister and I are fighting.

739
00:39:25,472 --> 00:39:27,474
We were yelling at each other.

740
00:39:27,474 --> 00:39:28,809
Ma...

741
00:39:29,851 --> 00:39:32,145
Sis, please stop fighting.

742
00:39:32,145 --> 00:39:35,482
Just talk and work
things out with Mommy.

743
00:39:38,235 --> 00:39:39,945
Sweetheart, listen to Mommy, please.

744
00:39:39,945 --> 00:39:42,656
Please, listen to me.
Listen to me, baby.

745
00:39:43,365 --> 00:39:45,117
I promise you…

746
00:39:45,117 --> 00:39:48,745
when we get to the UK,
none of this will happen.

747
00:39:48,745 --> 00:39:51,373
No fighting, no yelling.

748
00:39:51,373 --> 00:39:54,793
You will not grow up ungrateful!

749
00:39:54,793 --> 00:39:56,294
UK?

750
00:39:56,795 --> 00:39:58,880
The UK again!

751
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:02,525
As if you’re so sure that
Agatha wants to go with you.

752
00:40:02,549 --> 00:40:05,011
Do you think it’s easy to
take care of a child?

753
00:40:05,428 --> 00:40:08,223
You’re so bold just because
we’re grown up now.

754
00:40:08,223 --> 00:40:10,475
Fine! Take Agatha!

755
00:40:10,475 --> 00:40:12,618
So you can experience what
it’s like to be a mother!

756
00:40:20,652 --> 00:40:21,652
Argh!

757
00:40:21,987 --> 00:40:22,987
Argh!

758
00:40:23,488 --> 00:40:24,990
- Argh!
- Miss!

759
00:40:24,990 --> 00:40:26,616
Go easy, please.

760
00:40:27,284 --> 00:40:29,161
Miss, can I just buy that?

761
00:40:29,161 --> 00:40:32,080
No, you can’t.
That dollhouse is for our prize pot.

762
00:40:33,665 --> 00:40:35,083
Hey, Miss!

763
00:40:35,083 --> 00:40:37,627
You’re done,
someone else is next.

764
00:41:05,780 --> 00:41:09,618
Whoo!

765
00:41:10,952 --> 00:41:12,746
Whoo!

766
00:41:16,086 --> 00:41:17,671
[wailing]

767
00:41:21,630 --> 00:41:23,298
I hate this life!

768
00:41:26,111 --> 00:41:31,908
Whoo!

769
00:41:44,616 --> 00:41:46,535
Why am I crying?

770
00:41:47,322 --> 00:41:50,158
I don’t want to do this anymore.

771
00:41:50,158 --> 00:41:51,409
I’m done.

772
00:41:51,409 --> 00:41:53,286
It’s embarrassing.

773
00:42:09,552 --> 00:42:10,553
Yeah.

774
00:42:10,553 --> 00:42:12,264
I hope things get better.

775
00:42:12,264 --> 00:42:14,099
They’ll understand.

776
00:42:14,099 --> 00:42:15,658
I hope it’s not too late.

777
00:42:16,184 --> 00:42:17,785
When will you be back home?

778
00:42:24,892 --> 00:42:26,226
I’ll call you later.

779
00:42:35,495 --> 00:42:36,621
Agatha?

780
00:42:38,397 --> 00:42:39,774
Agatha?!

781
00:42:40,875 --> 00:42:42,460
Agatha!

782
00:42:43,295 --> 00:42:44,296
What?

783
00:42:44,296 --> 00:42:46,673
You didn’t even notice
your child is gone?

784
00:42:48,925 --> 00:42:50,302
Well, you're gone all night, right?

785
00:42:50,302 --> 00:42:51,428
What about you?

786
00:42:52,429 --> 00:42:53,638
You rarely act like a mom,

787
00:42:53,638 --> 00:42:55,390
and you still can’t play it right.

788
00:42:57,851 --> 00:42:59,060
Agatha…

789
00:43:00,687 --> 00:43:01,938
Agatha?

790
00:44:05,835 --> 00:44:07,170
Hello, Ma’am Ivy?

791
00:44:07,170 --> 00:44:10,423
Have you seen Agatha
there at the café?

792
00:44:12,884 --> 00:44:14,928
Oh, you closed early.

793
00:44:15,595 --> 00:44:19,307
I’ll just ask Mrs. Letty.
Maybe she went there to play.

794
00:44:19,933 --> 00:44:22,018
Alright. Just please let me know.

795
00:44:22,018 --> 00:44:23,228
Thank you.

796
00:44:33,029 --> 00:44:35,573
Aunt Steph, have you seen Agatha?

797
00:44:35,949 --> 00:44:38,159
Maybe she’s playing with Sarah?

798
00:44:39,160 --> 00:44:40,703
Oh, I see.

799
00:44:41,746 --> 00:44:44,749
Please let me know if you
see her. Thank you.

800
00:44:51,923 --> 00:44:53,299
Grandma's here.

801
00:45:00,390 --> 00:45:02,517
Where could she have gone?

802
00:45:06,855 --> 00:45:07,855
[clears throat]

803
00:45:14,612 --> 00:45:16,171
Is your sister really like that?

804
00:45:16,948 --> 00:45:19,008
Just running away like that?

805
00:45:19,492 --> 00:45:20,593
Just disappearing?

806
00:45:22,865 --> 00:45:24,158
I don’t know.

807
00:45:25,081 --> 00:45:26,849
You know her better than I do.

808
00:45:28,751 --> 00:45:30,336
You only hear the good news,

809
00:45:30,336 --> 00:45:32,313
so you don’t see that side of her.

810
00:45:42,724 --> 00:45:43,892
Mom...

811
00:45:45,435 --> 00:45:47,145
I’m here now.

812
00:45:49,105 --> 00:45:50,648
I’m sorry.

813
00:45:53,001 --> 00:45:54,711
It’s just that…

814
00:45:55,695 --> 00:45:57,838
there was a hurricane, and...

815
00:45:59,808 --> 00:46:01,968
all the flights were cancelled.

816
00:46:03,203 --> 00:46:06,789
I waited at the airport all night.

817
00:46:07,207 --> 00:46:08,208
[clears throat]

818
00:46:09,834 --> 00:46:13,338
If only I could’ve flown here myself,
I would have.

819
00:46:15,673 --> 00:46:18,259
I’m sorry I wasn’t
able to hold you

820
00:46:18,259 --> 00:46:21,179
or hug you during the times...

821
00:46:23,515 --> 00:46:26,601
you needed me to be there.

822
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:30,230
Mom…

823
00:46:31,439 --> 00:46:33,274
Please help me

824
00:46:33,274 --> 00:46:35,860
be a mother to my children.

825
00:46:43,159 --> 00:46:46,079
You know them better than I do.

826
00:46:46,663 --> 00:46:48,665
You’re their favorite.

827
00:46:49,666 --> 00:46:51,918
I can’t blame them.

828
00:46:56,673 --> 00:46:58,424
Oh my Lord, Mom...

829
00:47:02,679 --> 00:47:04,931
I miss you so much.

830
00:47:10,645 --> 00:47:11,854
[heavy sigh]

831
00:47:12,814 --> 00:47:13,940
Ma...

832
00:47:17,026 --> 00:47:18,506
Where would you want to be buried?

833
00:47:21,823 --> 00:47:22,949
Why?

834
00:47:23,992 --> 00:47:26,077
Are you going to my funeral?

835
00:47:26,786 --> 00:47:27,954
Yes.

836
00:47:28,580 --> 00:47:30,472
I'm not like you.

837
00:47:34,002 --> 00:47:35,394
I was hoping…

838
00:47:36,296 --> 00:47:38,006
to be buried here,

839
00:47:38,006 --> 00:47:39,841
beside your grandmother.

840
00:47:40,508 --> 00:47:41,551
But…

841
00:47:41,551 --> 00:47:43,720
But the fare is too expensive?

842
00:47:47,348 --> 00:47:48,516
But…

843
00:47:49,309 --> 00:47:51,618
my life is no longer here
in the Philippines.

844
00:47:55,940 --> 00:47:57,458
And I’m getting married.

845
00:47:58,568 --> 00:48:00,085
We already know that.

846
00:48:04,824 --> 00:48:06,717
I’m sorry for neglecting you.

847
00:48:07,619 --> 00:48:08,927
I’ll admit it.

848
00:48:10,580 --> 00:48:12,165
At first…

849
00:48:12,165 --> 00:48:13,666
yes,

850
00:48:13,666 --> 00:48:15,752
it was for the money.

851
00:48:16,628 --> 00:48:19,354
Because I wanted to
give you a good life.

852
00:48:23,718 --> 00:48:26,737
So I pushed through and
I endured it, even when…

853
00:48:28,222 --> 00:48:30,600
even when it was so hard.

854
00:48:31,434 --> 00:48:34,312
Even when I couldn’t anymore.

855
00:48:34,312 --> 00:48:36,731
And then I didn’t expect that…

856
00:48:38,816 --> 00:48:41,486
I would find myself there.

857
00:48:42,862 --> 00:48:46,115
That my heart would
finally feel full there.

858
00:48:47,367 --> 00:48:50,745
But in finding space for myself,

859
00:48:50,745 --> 00:48:53,972
I lost my place in your lives.

860
00:48:55,416 --> 00:48:57,001
Because of me.

861
00:48:58,503 --> 00:49:00,046
I’m sorry.

862
00:49:03,591 --> 00:49:06,302
If I didn’t listen to you,

863
00:49:06,302 --> 00:49:08,846
if I didn’t tell you...

864
00:49:08,846 --> 00:49:10,932
how much I love you—

865
00:49:12,475 --> 00:49:14,852
how much I love all of you.

866
00:49:18,356 --> 00:49:20,692
How proud I am of you

867
00:49:20,692 --> 00:49:23,069
for stepping up...

868
00:49:24,445 --> 00:49:27,407
through all my shortcomings.

869
00:49:27,865 --> 00:49:30,451
It hurts because my apologies

870
00:49:30,451 --> 00:49:32,286
can’t change anything anymore.

871
00:49:35,415 --> 00:49:37,208
It hurts that…

872
00:49:41,118 --> 00:49:43,287
I’m still alive, but...

873
00:49:44,674 --> 00:49:47,260
it’s like I’m already
dead to you.

874
00:49:48,970 --> 00:49:51,363
I had to make you feel that
I accepted you’re gone.

875
00:49:53,993 --> 00:49:55,953
Because it felt like…

876
00:49:57,729 --> 00:49:59,580
I waited for you my whole life.

877
00:50:03,305 --> 00:50:05,558
I got tired of being hurt.

878
00:50:10,283 --> 00:50:13,010
I had to become strong so that…

879
00:50:14,662 --> 00:50:17,681
I could live without
my mom by my side.

880
00:50:19,417 --> 00:50:20,668
Mommy?

881
00:50:26,299 --> 00:50:27,467
Blessie...

882
00:50:28,009 --> 00:50:29,943
Can I hold you?

883
00:50:33,097 --> 00:50:34,948
Just this once, please.

884
00:50:46,152 --> 00:50:49,588
Am I still your Mommy,
even now that you’re grown?

885
00:50:56,746 --> 00:50:57,997
Even if...

886
00:50:57,997 --> 00:51:00,833
you don’t want to call me
“Mommy” anymore?

887
00:51:02,710 --> 00:51:04,629
I’m okay, Ma.

888
00:51:05,797 --> 00:51:07,231
Don’t worry.

889
00:51:08,966 --> 00:51:12,094
If… if you can’t come back to
the Philippines anymore,

890
00:51:12,094 --> 00:51:13,695
when you’re gone…

891
00:51:14,138 --> 00:51:16,323
I’ll lay here beside Grandma.

892
00:51:20,019 --> 00:51:21,604
Not so soon, my dear.

893
00:51:21,604 --> 00:51:23,121
I’ll go first.

894
00:51:29,529 --> 00:51:32,673
Don’t you really want
to come with me?

895
00:51:34,742 --> 00:51:36,452
I don’t know, Ma.

896
00:51:40,373 --> 00:51:42,960
I don’t even know
what I want in life.

897
00:51:45,586 --> 00:51:47,547
But maybe…

898
00:51:47,547 --> 00:51:50,174
I’ll stay here for now.

899
00:51:50,174 --> 00:51:51,717
Because...

900
00:51:51,717 --> 00:51:53,511
for the longest time,

901
00:51:54,220 --> 00:51:56,639
all I ever thought about
was Grandma,

902
00:51:57,598 --> 00:51:59,559
and Agatha.

903
00:52:00,935 --> 00:52:03,229
I never thought about myself.

904
00:52:05,064 --> 00:52:06,357
[phone ringing]

905
00:52:10,653 --> 00:52:11,654
Hello?

906
00:52:11,654 --> 00:52:14,365
Blessie, I saw Agatha at the fair.

907
00:52:14,699 --> 00:52:15,867
She’s here.

908
00:52:15,867 --> 00:52:17,118
Alright, okay.

909
00:52:17,118 --> 00:52:18,786
Please keep an eye on her
we’re on our way.

910
00:52:18,786 --> 00:52:20,121
Ma, let’s go.

911
00:52:41,309 --> 00:52:42,602
Hey!

912
00:52:45,021 --> 00:52:46,480
Wow!

913
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:47,732
How did you get that?

914
00:52:47,732 --> 00:52:50,192
You just didn't
have faith in me.

915
00:52:50,192 --> 00:52:51,944
Oh, you…

916
00:52:51,944 --> 00:52:54,572
I’m your number one supporter,
you know.

917
00:52:55,156 --> 00:52:57,575
Really? If you had
just listened to me,

918
00:52:57,575 --> 00:53:00,690
we would’ve taken
this home a long time ago.

919
00:53:13,382 --> 00:53:15,051
Sorry.

920
00:53:16,427 --> 00:53:18,612
Sorry, I didn’t listen to you.

921
00:53:19,722 --> 00:53:22,725
Shouldn’t we be happy
we’re all together?

922
00:53:22,725 --> 00:53:24,852
Now what? You two made up?

923
00:53:26,437 --> 00:53:27,647
Yeah.

924
00:53:28,022 --> 00:53:30,816
See? You’ll only make up
when I’m not around.

925
00:53:30,816 --> 00:53:31,984
You’re so silly.

926
00:53:31,984 --> 00:53:33,778
You're doing that, huh.

927
00:53:36,255 --> 00:53:37,787
- Sis.
- Hmm?

928
00:53:37,794 --> 00:53:41,386
Sorry for making your life harder.

929
00:53:41,410 --> 00:53:43,428
If I hadn’t gotten sick back then,

930
00:53:44,372 --> 00:53:46,598
Mommy would’ve come home sooner.

931
00:53:48,042 --> 00:53:50,143
Maybe you wouldn’t
be this bitter.

932
00:53:51,295 --> 00:53:54,507
Sorry for taking your childhood away.

933
00:53:56,008 --> 00:53:57,760
Ew! You know what?

934
00:53:57,760 --> 00:54:00,137
You’re so dramatic.

935
00:54:00,137 --> 00:54:01,613
You’re so cheesy.

936
00:54:01,931 --> 00:54:03,265
Oh, you…

937
00:54:03,265 --> 00:54:05,434
Alright, that’s enough, okay?

938
00:54:05,434 --> 00:54:07,937
I’m gonna tickle you!
Want that?

939
00:54:07,937 --> 00:54:09,438
Anyway...

940
00:54:09,438 --> 00:54:10,940
Agatha...

941
00:54:11,482 --> 00:54:13,333
if you want to go with Mommy,

942
00:54:14,026 --> 00:54:15,252
that’s okay, alright?

943
00:54:15,653 --> 00:54:16,962
I love you, Sis.

944
00:54:17,488 --> 00:54:18,672
Come over here.

945
00:54:19,865 --> 00:54:21,075
Come here.

946
00:54:24,745 --> 00:54:26,789
- Let’s play.
- Okay.

947
00:54:26,789 --> 00:54:28,082
- Let’s go play.
- Nice one!

948
00:54:28,082 --> 00:54:29,333
- How did you get it?
- Yeah!

949
00:54:29,333 --> 00:54:30,960
That was just one try.

950
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:32,044
One try?

951
00:54:32,044 --> 00:54:33,879
- Yes.
- I don’t believe you.

952
00:54:33,879 --> 00:54:36,382
- I’m telling you, just one try!
- I still don’t believe you.

953
00:54:36,382 --> 00:54:37,925
Let’s put this here.

954
00:54:37,925 --> 00:54:39,677
- Yes.
- There.

955
00:54:39,677 --> 00:54:41,387
Perfect.

956
00:54:44,682 --> 00:54:47,226
- It’s pretty.
- Can I join?

957
00:54:47,935 --> 00:54:49,228
Mommy!

958
00:55:05,411 --> 00:55:06,871
Come on, let’s play.

959
00:55:06,871 --> 00:55:09,040
Wait. Just a second. Hold on.

960
00:55:09,040 --> 00:55:10,791
Uh, five minutes.

961
00:55:10,791 --> 00:55:12,001
Okay, two. Just two.

962
00:55:12,001 --> 00:55:13,627
One. Just one.

963
00:55:13,627 --> 00:55:15,671
One, two, three.

964
00:55:15,671 --> 00:55:17,965
Red carpet for Mommy.

965
00:55:17,965 --> 00:55:18,965
Go.

966
00:55:19,800 --> 00:55:22,053
- There you go.
- Yay!

967
00:55:22,053 --> 00:55:24,680
[everyone] Yay!
